ar%20to%20come%20up%20with%20the%20%24454%20million%20bond%2C%20due%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20such%20bonds%20would%20be%20underwritten%20by%20an%20insurer%20or%20specialized%20bond%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Trump's%20lawyers%20say%20that%20after%20approaching%2030%20such%20companies%2C%20none%20will%20take%20the%20ex-president's%20real-estate%20holdings%20as%20collateral%2C%20creating%20a%20%26quot%3Bpractical%20impossibility%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20a%20bond%2C%20they%20wrote%20in%20court%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20federal%20prosecutor%20Andrew%20Weissmann%20told%20AFP%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20seems%20pretty%20clear%20to%20me%2C%20based%20on%20the%20filings%2C%20that%20the%20problem%20he%20is%20having%20is%20that%20whatever%20assets%20he%20has%20are%20already%20leveraged%26quot%3B%20against%20other%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump%20cannot%20pay%2C%20added%20Carl%20Tobias%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Richmond%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe%20confronts%20the%20prospect%20of%20humiliation%20and%20serious%20financial%20harm.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultiple%20appeals%20are%20ongoing%20by%20the%20ex-president%20--%20who%20has%20denounced%20the%20judge%20who%20issued%20the%20ruling%20as%20%26quot%3Bcrooked%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20%26quot%3BTrump%20Hater%26quot%3B%20--%20including%20one%20at%20the%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%2030-day%20grace%20period%20to%20put%20up%20the%20money%20expires%20Monday%2C%20raising%20the%20prospect%20that%20unless%20courts%20intervene%20or%20the%20New%20York%20attorney%20general%20gives%20him%20more%20time%2C%20Trump%20might%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bsell%20his%20properties%20or%20related%20assets%2C%20attempt%20to%20secure%20a%20bank%20loan%2C%20or%20even%20declare%20bankruptcy%2C%26quot%3B%20Tobias%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20even%20bankruptcy%20wouldn't%20stop%20authorities%20from%20claiming%20Trump's%20money%2C%20with%20the%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James%20able%20to%20freeze%20his%20accounts%20or%20even%20seize%20certain%20properties%20related%20to%20the%20case%2C%20Tobias%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20mortgage%20or%20sell%20great%20assets%2C%20perhaps%20at%20fire%20sale%20prices%2C%20and%20if%20and%20when%20I%20win%20the%20appeal%2C%20they%20would%20be%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BElection%20interference!%26quot%3B%20he%20charged%20in%20another%20post%2C%20while%20also%20calling%20James%2C%20who%20is%20a%20Democrat%2C%20%26quot%3Bcorrupt%20and%20racist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%20Trump%20offered%20a%20%24100%20million%20bond%20to%20partially%20cover%20him%20as%20he%20appealed%20--%20a%20move%20rejected%20by%20a%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court%20Appellate%20Division%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20fraud%20ruling%2C%20Trump%20was%20also%20banned%20from%20running%20businesses%20in%20New%20York%20state%20for%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20barred%20from%20seeking%20loans%20from%20institutions%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20though%20a%20judge%20has%20lifted%20that%20part%20of%20the%20ruling%20as%20Trump%20seeks%20to%20secure%20his%20bond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%2C%20facing%2091%20criminal%20counts%20in%20other%20cases%2C%20has%20seized%20on%20his%20legal%20woes%20to%20fire%20up%20supporters%20and%20denounce%20his%20likely%20opponent%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20claiming%20that%20court%20cases%20are%20%26quot%3Bjust%20a%20way%20of%20hurting%20me%20in%20the%20election.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711061280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2F8l68b4e8_donald-trump-afp_625x300_17_Ja