20during%20discussions%20on%20the%20Delhi%20Health%20Establishments%20(Registration%20and%20Regulation)%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20is%20troubling%20us%20is%20that%20the%20petitioner%20is%20highlighting%20the%20plight%20of%20a%20common%20man.%20He%20is%20telling%20us%20that%20all%20sorts%20of%20lab%20reports%20are%20being%20generated%20which%20are%20not%20true%20and%20correct%20and%20the%20common%20man%20is%20suffering.%20But%20it%20is%20your%20game%20of%20one-upmanship%20between%20the%20two%20of%20you%20and%20between%20the%20various%20factions%20that%20is%20going%20on.%20This%20is%20unacceptable%20to%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20be%20practical%20and%20ensure%20that%20the%20touts%20do%20not%20benefit%20from%20the%20fight%20between%20these%20two%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20bench%20of%20Acting%20Chief%20Justice%20Manmohan%20and%20Justice%20Manmeet%20PS%20Arora%20said%2C%20asking%20them%20not%20to%20indulge%20in%20%26quot%3Bbrinkmanship%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20if%20the%20minister%20and%20the%20secretary%20are%20incapable%20of%20handling%20the%20issues%20and%20keep%20on%20bickering%2C%20the%20court%20will%20ask%20a%20third%20party%20to%20handle%20things%20or%20pass%20an%20order%20about%20what%20has%20to%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20do%20this%20with%20us%20otherwise%20you%20both%20will%20go%20to%20jail.%20We%20will%20have%20no%20hesitation%20in%20sending%20both%20of%20you%20to%20jail%20if%20the%20common%20man%20benefits%20from%20this.%20Both%20of%20you%20can't%20have%20large%20egos%2C%20you%20both%20are%20servants%20of%20the%20government%20and%20you%20both%20have%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20common%20man%20benefits.%20What%20are%20you%20doing%3F%20People%20are%20getting%20wrong%20reports%20of%20their%20blood%20samples%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20was%20hearing%20a%202018%20petition%20by%20Bejon%20Kumar%20Misra%2C%20represented%20by%20advocate%20Shashank%20Deo%20Sudhi%2C%20who%20has%20alleged%20that%20unauthorised%20laboratories%20and%20diagnostic%20centres%20were%20functioning%20in%20the%20national%20capital%20with%20unqualified%20technicians%20and%20giving%20incorrect%20reports%20to%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20minister%20said%20the%20Delhi%20Health%20Bill%20was%20finalised%20in%20May%202022%20itself%2C%20the%20high%20court%20asked%20why%20it%20was%20not%20yet%20sent%20to%20the%20Centre%20for%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20if%20this%20was%20going%20to%20take%20time%2C%20the%20Delhi%20government%20should%20consider%20implementing%20the%20central%20government%20statute-%20The%20Clinical%20Establishments%20(Registration%20and%20Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20submission%20made%20by%20Mr%20Bharadwaj%20that%20the%20court's%20indulgence%20will%20help%20the%20government%20to%20get%20the%20bill%20enacted%20irked%20the%20court%20which%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20think%20we%20are%20a%20pawn%20in%20this%20game%20and%20you%20will%20use%20this%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20strategy.%20We%20are%20not%20anyone's%20pawn%2C%20cure%20this%20misconception%20that%20you%20will%20use%20the%20court's%20process%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%20had%20argued%20before%20the%20court%20that%20pathological%20labs%20in%20the%20city%20are%20unregulated%20and%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20lives%20of%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plea%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSuch%20illegal%20labs%20continue%20to%20mushroom%20in%20and%20around%20Delhi-NCT%20and%20it%20can%20be%20easily%20estimated%20that%20the%20total%20number%20of%20such%20illegal%20pathological%20and%20diagnostic%20labs%20can%20be%20anywhere%20between%2020%2C000%20and%2025%2C000%2C%20and%20every%20street%20in%20the%20capital%20has%20such%20illegal%20pathological%20labs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711041660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fv219irn8_saurabh-bharadwaj_625x300_21_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fwill-send-you-to-jail-high-court-warns-delhi-minister-saurabh-bharadwaj-5285330%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Admonishing%20the%20Delhi%20health%20minister%20and%20health%20secretary%20for%20not%20complying%20with%20judicial%20orders%20on%20the%20enactment%20of%20a%20law%20to%20regulate%20clinical%20establishments%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20on%20Thursday%20warned%20them%20that%20they%20could%20be%20sent%20to%20jail.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fwill-send-you-to-jail-high-court-warns-delhi-minister-saurabh-bharadwaj-5285330%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fwill-send-you-to-jail-high-court-warns-delhi-minister-saurabh-bharadwaj-5285330%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fwill-send-you-to-jail-high-court-warns-delhi-minister-saurabh-bharadwaj-5285330%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Were%20the%20Top%20Buyers%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Paying%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F21224008%2Frupixen-EsH_VBiZhVA-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%E2%80%99ve%20known%20for%20a%20few%20weeks%20now%20who%20the%20top%20purchasers%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20were%2C%20and%20which%20parties%20(or%20party%2C%20given%20the%20way%20the%20numbers%20stack%20up)%20benefit%20the%20most.%20But%20thanks%20to%20the%20latest%20data%20released%20on%20Thursday%20evening%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20and%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20we%20can%20now%20match%20which%20corporates%20were%20donating%20to%20which%20parties%2C%20and%20when.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20first%20analysis%20on%20the%20latest%20data%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20the%20top%20buyers%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20who%20they%20were%20donating%20to%20using%20this%20opaque%20tool.%20This%20data%20pertains%20to%20the%20period%20beginning%20from%20April%2012%2C%202019%20and%20till%20January%2015%2C%202024%20(when%20the%20last%20bonds%20were%20sold).%20It%20does%20not%20contain%20data%20from%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20three%20of%20these%20fives%20groups%2Fcompanies%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20received%20the%20largest%20portion%20of%20donations.%20For%20the%20other%20two%2C%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20received%20the%20most%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F17253290%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F17253290%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F17253290%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMegha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructures%20Limited%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructures%20Limited%20is%20the%20second%20biggest%20donor%20to%20political%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20between%20April%2012%2C%202019%20and%20January%2011%2C%202024%2C%20new%20data%20reveals%20it%20is%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20donor%20at%20Rs%20584%20crore.%20The%20Telangana-based%20company%20chairman%20Pamireddy%20Pichi%20Reddy%20and%20his%20nephew%20P.V.%20Krishna%20Reddy%20donated%20Rs%20966%20crore%20during%20this%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20data%20released%20by%20the%20ECI%20on%20Thursday%20reveals%20that%20out%20of%20the%20Rs%20966%20crore%2C%20it%20gave%20a%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20which%20received%20Rs%20584%20crore%20from%20MIEL.%20The%20second%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20by%20MIEL%20was%20the%20ruling%20K.%20Chandrasekhara%20Rao-led%20Bharath%20Rashtra%20Samiti%2C%20which%20received%20Rs%20195%20crore%2C%20while%20its%20Andhra%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20counterpart%20YSR%20Congress%20got%20Rs%2037%20crore%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20received%20Rs%2085%20crores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMIEL%20also%20donated%20to%20Nitish%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%2C%20the%20ruling%20party%20in%20Bihar%2C%20an%20amount%20of%20Rs%2010%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMIEL%20also%20donated%20to%20opposition%20parties%20but%20only%20a%20small%20part%20of%20its%20chunk%20of%20electoral%20bonds.%20The%20Andhra-based%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20received%20Rs%2028%20crore%3B%20the%20Congress%20got%20Rs%2018%20crore%2C%20while%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20received%20Rs%205%20crore.%20The%20Pawan%20Kalyan-led%20Jana%20Sena%20Party%20also%20got%20Rs%204%20crores%20from%20MIEL.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-based-megha-was-top-donor-to-jds-maximum-bonds-came-for-2023-karnataka-polls%5C%22%3Ethe%20submissions%20of%20political%20parties%20to%20the%20ECI%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular)%20also%20received%20Rs%2050%20crore%2C%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%2089.75%20crore%2C%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20from%20MIEL%20before%20April%2012%2C%202023%20%E2%80%93%20nearly%2056%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations%20it%20received%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20Karnataka%20assembly%20elections%20in%20May%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%20that%20MIEL%20landed%20multiple%20government%20infrastructure%20projects%20during%20this%20period%2C%20too.%20The%20company%20secured%20the%20tender%20for%20Rs%2014%2C400%20crore%20Thane-Borivali%20twin%20tunnel%20project%2C%20which%20incidentally%20also%20came%20a%20month%20after%20it%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20140%20crore%20on%20April%2011%2C%202023.%20Out%20of%20the%20Rs%20140%20crore%2C%20Rs%20115%20crore%20were%20donated%20by%20the%20MIEL%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20while%20it%20distributed%20the%20remaining%20Rs%2025%20crore%20between%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%2C%20Jana%20Sena%20Party%2C%20Congress%2C%20and%20Janata%20Dal%20(Secular).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20tender%20process%20became%20controversial%20back%20then.%20The%20Maharashtra%20government%E2%80%99s%20Mumbai%20Metropolitan%20Development%20Authority%20(MMRDA)%E2%80%99s%20tender%20for%20two%20road%20tunnels%20under%20the%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%20National%20Park%20in%20January%202023%2C%20in%20which%20only%20MEIL%E2%80%99s%20bid%20was%20found%20responsive.%20MIEL%E2%80%99s%20competitor%20L%26amp%3BT%20had%20challenged%20the%20decision%20in%20the%20court%20in%20May%202023%2C%20soon%20after%20MIEL%20secured%20the%20contract%2C%20but%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20dismissed%20its%20pleas%20on%20technical%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMIEL%20grew%20from%20a%20tiny%20company%20to%20become%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20infrastructure%20giants%20in%20India%2C%20with%20a%20footprint%20in%20over%2020%20states%20currently.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20big%20projects%20that%20it%20landed%20have%20mostly%20run%20into%20controversy.%20The%20newly-elected%20Congress%20chief%20minister%20of%20Telangana%20A.%20Revanth%20Reddy%2C%20while%20in%20opposition%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20had%20aggressively%20campaigned%20against%20the%20ruling%20BRS%20for%20its%20alleged%20irregularities%20in%20handing%20over%20several%20contracts%20in%20the%20gigantic%20Kaleshwaram%20Lift%20Irrigation%20project%20worth%20Rs%201%20lakh%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20other%20Telugu-speaking%20state%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Y.S.%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%20as%20an%20opposition%20leader%20between%202014%20to%202019%20had%20accused%20the%20N.%20Chandrababu%20Naidu-led%20TDP%20government%20of%20doing%20favours%20to%20MIEL%20in%20the%20massive%20Pattiseema%20irrigation%20project.%20However%2C%20Jagan%2C%20after%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20also%20awarded%20multiple%20contracts%20to%20MIEL%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20being%20some%20big%20contracts%20in%20the%20Polavaram%20Dam%20project%20which%20he%20did%20by%20cancelling%20the%20contract%20with%20Navayuga%20Engineering%2C%20yet%20another%20company%20that%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2055%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20MIEL%20is%20also%20under%20the%20scanner%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20department.%20Its%20office%20premises%20were%20raided%20in%20October%2C%202019%2C%20following%20which%20its%20purchase%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20continued%20at%20a%20massive%20scale.%20The%20company%20secured%20a%20project%20worth%20Rs%204%2C509%20crore%20in%20August%202020%20to%20construct%20the%20Zozi-la%20tunnel%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMIEL%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20has%20also%20ventured%20into%20the%20media%20industry%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Hyderabad-based%20My%20Home%20Group.%20It%20acquired%20the%20influential%20TV9TElugu%20channel%20and%20bought%2022%25%20stake%20in%20NTV%20channel.%20MIEL%20has%20declared%20big%20plans%20to%20enter%20electric%20vehicles%20manufacturing%20businesses%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFuture%20Gaming%20and%20Hotel%20Services%20Pvt.%20Ltd.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Lottery%20king%E2%80%99%20Santiago%20Martin%E2%80%99s%20company%2C%20Future%20Gaming%20and%20Hotel%20Services%20Pvt.%20Ltd.%2C%20was%20the%20single%20largest%20donor%20of%20funds%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20between%20April%202019%20and%20January%202022%2C%20at%20Rs%201%2C368%20crore.%20However%2C%20only%20Rs%20100%20crore%20of%20the%20total%20amount%20was%20donated%20to%20the%20ruling%20BJP%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fresh%20data%20uploaded%20on%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20website%20shows%20that%20of%20all%20the%20donations%20made%2C%20the%20ruling%20Trinamool%20Congress%20Party%20of%20West%20Bengal%20gained%20the%20highest%20amount%20at%20Rs%20542%20crore.%20The%20second%20largest%20donation%20of%20Rs%20503%20crore%20was%20made%20to%20the%20ruling%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Two%20other%20parties%20that%20received%20sizeable%20donations%20include%20YSR%20Congress%20at%20Rs%20154%20crore%20and%20Congress%20at%20Rs%2050%20crore.%20A%20small%20share%20went%20to%20Sikkim-based%20parties%2C%20at%20Rs%208%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20other%20donors%2C%20Future%20Gaming%20too%20has%20been%20under%20the%20ED%20scanner.%20On%20July%2023%2C%202019%2C%20the%20ED%20had%20attached%20assets%20worth%20Rs%20120%20crore%20in%20an%20alleged%20money%20laundering%20scam%2C%20where%20he%20was%20accused%20of%20inflating%20prize%20money%20and%20amassing%20property%20from%20unaccounted%20cash.%20The%20ED%20had%20carried%20out%20searches%20at%2070%20premises%20associated%20with%20the%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Comptroller%20and%20Audit%20General%20of%20India%20(CAG)%20too%20has%20flagged%20serious%20irregularities%20by%20marketing%20agents%2C%20including%20Future%20Gaming%20and%20Hotel%20Services%20owned%20by%20Martin%2C%20in%20a%202017%20report%20submitted%20to%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20audit%20was%20made%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%20in%202015%20following%20complaints%20of%20corruption%20and%20violations%20in%20lotteries%2C%20with%20Martin%20being%20a%20major%20player.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVedanta%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EData%20published%20by%20the%20SBI%20on%20March%2021%20%E2%80%93%20replete%20with%20the%20alphanumeric%20bond%20numbers%20this%20time%2C%20and%20the%20dates%20they%20were%20encashed%20%E2%80%93%20reveals%20that%20mining%20giant%20Vedanta%20Limited%20donated%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20250.15%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20all%20electoral%20bonds%20bought%20by%20Vedanta%20(worth%20Rs%20400.65%20crores%20in%20total)%20thus%20went%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20was%20the%20biggest%20benefactor%20of%20all%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20that%20Vedanta%20bought%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Congress%20(Rs%20125%20crore)%2C%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(Rs%2040%20crore)%20and%20the%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha%20(Rs%205%20crore).%20The%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20received%20only%20Rs%200.3%20crore%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20from%20Vedanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVedanta%20is%20the%20fourth%20largest%20buyer%20of%20electoral%20bonds.%20As%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmining-giant-vedanta-bought-electoral-bonds-worth-rs-400-65-crore%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20reported%20earlier%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Vedanta%20donated%20Rs%20400.65%20crore%20to%20unnamed%20parties%20(the%20data%20on%20which%20parties%20it%20donated%20to%20via%20electoral%20bonds%20had%20not%20been%20available%20then).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVedanta%20Limited%20has%20been%20regularly%20pulled%20up%20for%20environmental%20violations%20across%20several%20of%20its%20mining%20and%20oil%20and%20gas%20projects%20in%20India%2C%20including%20in%20Barmer%2C%20Rajasthan.%20Vedanta%20also%20acquired%20a%20steel%20plant%20in%20Jharkhand%20in%20June%202018.%20The%20company%2C%20ESL%20Steel%20Limited%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsclick.in%2Fblame-game-after-locals-seeking-jobs-vedantas-bokaro-steel-plant-beaten%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%20in%20the%20news%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20November%20last%20year%20due%20to%20clashes%20between%20locals%20and%20Vedanta%E2%80%99s%20security%20guards%20after%20the%20former%20staged%20a%20protest%20outside%20the%20steel%20plant%E2%80%99s%20gates%20to%20demand%20more%20jobs%20for%20local%20communities%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirms%20linked%20to%20Mahendra%20K.%20Jalan%20and%20family%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ffirms-linked-to-kolkata-industrialist-mahendra-jalan-spent-rs-617-crore-on-electoral-bonds%5C%22%3Ehas%20reported%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20four%20firms%20linked%20to%20Kolkata-based%20industrialist%20Mahendra%20K.%20Jalan%20and%20his%20family%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20616.92%20crore%20between%20April%202019%20and%20January%202024.%20This%20makes%20the%20group%20the%20third-highest%20political%20funder.%20The%20four%20companies%20are%20Keventer%20Foodpark%20Infra%20Limited%2C%20Madanlal%20Ltd%2C%20MKJ%20Enterprises%20Ltd%20and%20Sasmal%20Infrastructure%20Private%20Limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20data%20shows%20that%20these%20companies%20donated%20to%20a%20range%20of%20political%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20the%20BJP%2C%20Congress%2C%20TMC%2C%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%2C%20Samajwadi%20Party%2C%20AAP%2C%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%2C%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20and%20Jharkhand%20Mukti%20Morcha.%20The%20highest%20amount%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%20%E2%80%93%20at%20Rs%20351.92%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20followed%20by%20the%20Congress%20with%20Rs%20160.6%20crore.%20The%20TMC%20received%20the%20third%20highest%20amount%20from%20the%20group%2C%20at%20Rs%2065.9%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Snigdhendu%20Bhattacharya%20has%20written%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CJalan%20was%20known%20as%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fmahendra-jalan-pulls-out-of-tide-water-race%2Fcid%2F887214%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fbusiness%2Fmahendra-jalan-pulls-out-of-tide-water-race%2Fcid%2F887214%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710595078224000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw03GErm1LL9zb2X4u7WKRb0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%20baron%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20new%20century.%C2%A0After%20that%2C%C2%A0he%20expanded%20significantly%20in%20the%20dairy%2C%20agro%20and%20food%20processing%20sectors.%20By%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Fheart-of-kolkata-set-to-get-its-first-helipad-on-33-storey-skyscraper%2Farticleshow%2F93625848.cms%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Fheart-of-kolkata-set-to-get-its-first-helipad-on-33-storey-skyscraper%2Farticleshow%2F93625848.cms%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710595078224000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1sMwnlUznsmDuUVjMUDCQy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jalan%20was%20planning%20to%20build%20a%2033-storied%20building%20in%20Kolkata%E2%80%99s%20Hooghly%20(Ganga)%20river%20facing%20Strand%20Road%2C%20one%20of%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20central%20business%20districts%2C%20and%20to%20top%20it%20with%20a%20helipad%20on%20its%20roof.%20The%20project%20is%20in%20the%20pipeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CJalan%20maintained%20good%20rapport%20with%20both%20BJP%20and%20the%20TMC%20since%202013.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rediff.com%2Fmoney%2Freport%2Fwhy-some-bengal-industrialists-are-avoiding-modi%2F20130409.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EModi%20was%20yet%20to%20come%20to%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fcurrent-affairs%2Fmodi-blasts-the-left-upa-but-showers-mamata-on-tmc-113040900354_1.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20few%20businessmen%20to%20attend%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20meet%20in%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20was%20also%20attending%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Jalan%20is%20not%20part%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20of%20all%20four%20firms%20that%20purchased%20the%20bonds.%20In%20some%20of%20them%2C%20Radheshyam%20Khetan%20is%20in%20charge.%20Khetan%20is%20part%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20of%20Madanlal%20Limited%20and%20MKJ%20Enterprises%20Limited.%20He%20serves%20as%20the%20Chief%20Operating%20Officer%20of%20Keventer%20Projects%20Limited%2C%20a%20group%20company%20of%20Madanlal%20Limited.%20Madanlal%20Ltd%20is%20engaged%20in%20the%20purchase%20and%20sale%20of%20securities%20and%20the%20real%20estate%20sector%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20profile.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQwik%20Supply%20Chain%20Private%20Limited%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQwik%20Supply%20Chain%20Private%20Limited%20paid%20Rs%20375%20crore%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20Rs%2010%20crore%20to%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20and%20Rs%2025%20crore%20to%20the%20Shiv%20Sena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20not%20listed%20as%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20Reliance%2C%20but%20a%20strong%20Reliance%20imprint%20is%20visible.%20The%20company%E2%80%99s%20two%20present%20directors%20are%20Vipul%20Pranlal%20Mehta%20and%20Tapas%20Mitra.%20According%20to%20Zauba%20Corp%2C%20Tapas%20Mitra%20is%20also%20the%20director%20of%20Reliance%20Oil%20and%20Petroleum%2C%20Reliance%20Eros%20Productions%2C%20Reliance%20Photo%20Films%2C%20Reliance%20Fire%20Brigades%2C%20Ral%20Investment%20Private%20Limited%2C%20Reliance%20First%20Private%20Limited%20and%20Reliance%20Polyester%2C%20among%20others.%20Over%2050%25%20of%20the%20stake%20in%20Qwik%20Supply%20is%20held%20by%20three%20Reliance%20Group%20companies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Fqwik-top-buyer-indian-electoral-bonds-is-affiliated-ambanis-reliance-filings-2024-03-15%2F%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20third%20highest%20of%20bond%20purchasers%20among%20the%20individual%20companies%20that%20have%20bought%20bonds%20since%202018.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ftop-electoral-bond-purchasers-include-some-companies-that-were-raided-or-under-the-scanner%5C%22%3Ereported%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20earlier%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20SBI%20data%20had%20already%20revealed%20earlier%20that%20this%20Mumbai-based%20company%20had%20bought%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20410%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20information%20available%20on%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zaubacorp.com%2Fcompany%2FQWIK-SUPPLY-CHAIN-PRIVATE-LIMITED%2FU51100MH2000PTC129528%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Zauba%20Corp%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20was%20founded%2023%20years%20ago%20in%202000.%20Qwik%20Supply%20Chain%2C%20made%20its%20first%20purchase%20of%20bonds%20on%20January%205%2C%202022.%20The%20second%20batch%20of%20purchases%20continued%20five%20days%20later%2C%20on%20January%2010.%20The%20purchase%20then%20followed%20on%20November%2011%2C%202022%20and%20a%20year%20later%20on%20November%2017%2C%202023.%20All%20electoral%20bond%20purchases%20were%20made%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20according%20to%20details%20uploaded%20on%20Zauba%20Corp%2C%20shows%20that%20they%20have%20an%20office%20space%20in%20Dhobi%20Talao%2C%20in%20South%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESanjiv%20Goenka%20group%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVarious%20companies%20of%20Kolkata-based%20billionaire%20industrialist%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20donated%20the%20highest%20to%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20calculation%20done%20on%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20data%20of%20the%20SBI%20shows%20that%20the%20group%20donated%20Rs%20422%20crore%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%20the%20TMC.%20To%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20donations%20were%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Rs%20127%20crore%20and%20Rs%2015%20crore%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkolkata-billionaire-sanjiv-goenkas-companies-spent-rs-664-crore-in-electoral-bonds-and-trusts%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%2C%20the%20group%20had%20been%20under%20the%20scanner%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20and%20the%20CBI.%20Bonds%20worth%20Rs%2040%20crore%20were%20purchased%20after%20the%20CBI%20investigation%20was%20initiated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20had%20bought%20the%20maximum%20bonds%20during%20March-April%202021%2C%20when%20assembly%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20The%20elections%20for%20state%20legislatures%20in%20Kerala%20and%20Assam%20also%20happened%20at%20around%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20five%20companies%20of%20the%20group%20which%20purchased%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20were%3A%20Haldia%20Energy%20Ltd%2C%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure%20Limited%20%2C%20Philips%20Carbon%20Black%20Ltd%2C%20Crescent%20Power%20Ltd%20and%20RPSG%20Ventures%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20two%20companies%20of%20the%20group%20had%20also%20been%20accused%20by%20the%20CAG%20of%20rigging%20coal%20auctions.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711041423000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F21224008%2Frupixen-EsH_VBiZhVA-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwho-were-the-top-buyers-of-elect